    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Pieter Nanninck to Miklós Oláh ([Leuven], 6 May [1538])</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Damião de Góis, who is handing over the letter, is not
                            only of noble birth but also has unparalleled erudition; if he has the
                            chance, Oláh should talk to him because Damião de Góis often says how
                            much he desires it.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nannius Domino Nicolao <del corresp="Olahus">Olacho</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Olaho</add> etc. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Salutem plurimam. Qui tibi meas litteras praefert,
                        <persName>Damianus a Goes</persName>,<note xml:id="note.1">Damião de Góis,
                        see <hi rend="smallcap">Polet</hi> 1936, 264 and 273; and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Feist Hirsch</hi> 1967.</note> est eques Lusitanus non
                    minus claritudine generis, quam humanitate morum et litteris et litteratorum
                    moribus insignis. Si patientur tuae occupationes, velim, illum in colloquium
                    admittes, senties illum morum sinceritate, candore, fide, humanitate, modestia
                    tibi simillimum. Saepius de te mecum loquitur, tuae consuetudinis cupidissimus
                    est. Bene vale, Optime Patrone. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Pridiae Nonas Maias. Raptim.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
